# Modelica Language Specification > Arrays > Scalar, Vector, Matrix, and Array Operator Functions > Standard Type Coercion
https://specification.modelica.org/maint/3.6/arrays.html#2vpmq38cyugmnepmepu2onjc4

### Standard Type Coercion

In all contexts that require an expression which is a subtype of `Real`, an expression which is a subtype of `Integer` can also be used;
the `Integer` expression is automatically converted to `Real`.

This also applies to arrays of `Real`, and for fields of record expressions. There is no similar rule for sub-typing.

[Example:

```
record RealR
  Real x,y;
end RealR;
record IntegerR
  Integer x,y;
end IntegerR;
parameter Integer a = 1;
Real y(start=a);           // Ok, a is automatically coerced to Real
RealR r1 = IntegerR(a, a); // Ok, record is automatically coerced
RealR r2 = RealR(a, a);    // Ok, a is automatically coerced to Real
```

]

