# Modelica Language Specification > Functions > Function Call > Functional Input Arguments
https://specification.modelica.org/maint/3.6/functions.html#27cbxgkde6p1gaa8ojdpte9qm

The `quadrature2` example below uses a function `integrand` that is a component as input argument according to case [3](#functional-argument:component "item 3 ‣ 12.4.2 Functional Input Arguments ‣ 12.4 Function Call ‣ Chapter 12 Functions ‣ Modelica® Language Specification version 3.6"):

```
function quadrature2 "Integrate function y = integrand(x) from x1 to x2"
  input Real x1;
  input Real x2;
  input Integrand integrand; // Integrand is a partial function type
  output Real integral;
algorithm
  integral :=
    quadrature(x1, (x1 + x2) / 2, integrand) +
    quadrature((x1 + x2) / 2, x2, integrand);
end quadrature2;
```

